    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "key_math_t",
      "x": 90,
      "y": 398,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 80,
      "text": "Step 3 — The key:  (G P_i)^T (G P_j)  =  P_i^T  G^T G  P_j  =  P_i^T  I  P_j  =  P_i^T P_j\n\nG is an orthogonal matrix (rotation)  →  G^T G = I  →  G cancels itself out!\nJust like how G^{-1} G = I: rotating right then rotating back = no change.",
      "originalText": "Step 3 — The key:  (G P_i)^T (G P_j)  =  P_i^T  G^T G  P_j  =  P_i^T  I  P_j  =  P_i^T P_j\n\nG is an orthogonal matrix (rotation)  →  G^T G = I  →  G cancels itself out!\nJust like how G^{-1} G = I: rotating right then rotating back = no change.",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "strokeColor": "#b91c1c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 32,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 33,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": "key_math",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
